HEADWORD: Discolith
<hw>Dis"co*lith</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a round
plate + <ets>-lith</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One of a
species of coccoliths, having an oval discoidal body, with a thick
strongly refracting rim, and a thinner central portion. One of them
measures about ⟦frac1x50000⟧ of an inch in its longest
diameter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

